message.content: One of the most significant events that happened in Monaco in the past 20 years was the wedding of Prince Albert II and Charlene Wittstock on July 1 and 2, 2011. The wedding was a highly anticipated event, attracting global attention and media coverage. It was a momentous occasion for the principality, as Prince Albert II, the reigning monarch, married Charlene Wittstock, a former South African Olympic swimmer. The wedding celebrations included various events, such as a civil ceremony, a religious ceremony, a gala dinner, and a public concert. The event showcased the glamour and prestige associated with Monaco and its royal family, further solidifying the principality's status as a prominent global destination.
